_a242e267-5d49-4a22-b5ce-1d67c617be7e"><p>The Final Grade Override allows y=
ou to enter a final grade for students that is different from the grade aut=
omatically calculated by Canvas in the Gradebook. You can enter a letter gr=
ade or a percentage. A letter grade results in the lower bound of the gradi=
ng scheme. A percentage is retained as the override score.</p><p>An overrid=
e can be applied to final grades in grading periods, but the overridden gra=
des from the grading period will not affect the student's total final cours=
e grade.</p><p>Students can view the overridden grade in their Grades page.=
 However, students will not know the score has been overridden.</p><p><stro=
ng>Notes:</strong></p><ul><li>Final Grade Override is currently a course op=
t-in feature. To enable the final grade override feature option, learn how =
to <a rel=3D"nofollow" href=3D"https://instructure.vanillacommunities.com/h=
ome/leaving?allowTrusted=3D1&amp;target=3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fcommunity.canvaslms=
.com%2Fdocs%2FDOC-13029-4152156575">manage course features</a>.</li><li>Whe=
n a grader, such as an instructor or TA, enables the Final Grade Override o=
ption, the Override column displays for all graders in the course. Likewise=
, the Override column will be hidden if disabled by another grader in the c=
ourse.</li><li>The override column is included in Gradebook exports and can=
 be changed with a Gradebook import.</li><li>If your SIS accepts final grad=
es through grade passback, any entered override grades are included in SIS =
syncs in place of the calculated final grade.</li><li>After the final grade=
 override feature option has been enabled in a course, both the Gradebook a=
nd Final Grade Override options cannot be disabled.</li><li>Your Canvas adm=
in may need to configure SIS sync settings for final grade overrides to cor=
rectly sync to your SIS.</li><li>When a final grade override is entered as =
a letter grade, the percentage score for the assignment is the lower limit =
of the range assigned to that letter grade in the grading scheme. For examp=
le, your course grading scheme may designate a range of 86% to 89% for a B+=
 letter grade. Entering a B+ for a final grade override assigns a percentag=
e of 86%. To ensure students receive a specific percentage for their final =
grade, enter the grade override as a percentage.</li></ul></div></div><h2 i=
d=3D"open-grades" data-id=3D"open-grades">Open Grades</h2><div><img src=3D"=
https://us.v-cdn.net/6038536/uploads/migrated/1JFBZCQ3REU7/dbf47cc7-a501-41=
3f-9991-70c86a025881.png" alt=3D"Open Grades" height=3D"230" width=3D"181" =
loading=3D"lazy" style=3D"height: 230px; width: 181px" class=3D"embedImage-=
img importedEmbed-img"></div><p>In Course Navigation, click the <strong>Gra=
des</strong> link.</p><h2 id=3D"open-gradebook-settings" data-id=3D"open-gr=
adebook-settings">Open Gradebook Settings</h2><div><img src=3D"https://us.v=
-cdn.net/6038536/uploads/migrated/ITLFEU6HDSZH/caf0f435-c3d7-4442-a225-79dd=
9322115f.png" alt=3D"Open Gradebook Settings" height=3D"60" width=3D"855" l=
oading=3D"lazy" style=3D"height: 60px; width: 855px" class=3D"embedImage-im=
g importedEmbed-img"></div><p>Click the <strong>Settings</strong> icon.</p>=
<h2 id=3D"select-final-grade-override" data-id=3D"select-final-grade-overri=
de">Select Final Grade Override</h2><div><img src=3D"https://us.v-cdn.net/6=
038536/uploads/migrated/KEF5RSCM465W/6db013aa-cd9b-471d-bec4-1190018c5565.p=
ng" alt=3D"Select Final Grade Override" height=3D"680" width=3D"801" loadin=
g=3D"lazy" style=3D"height: 680px; width: 801px" class=3D"embedImage-img im=
portedEmbed-img"></div><p>In Gradebook Settings, open the <strong>Advanced<=
/strong> tab [1] and then click the <strong>Allow final grade override</str=
ong> checkbox [2]. Click the <strong>Apply Settings</strong> button [3].</p=
><h2 id=3D"enter-override-grade" data-id=3D"enter-override-grade">Enter Ove=
rride Grade</h2><div><img src=3D"https://us.v-cdn.net/6038536/uploads/migra=
ted/K9AB2EXNCZD4/77251391-8662-46a7-974c-586080cdac60.png" alt=3D"Enter Ove=
rride Grade" height=3D"313" width=3D"414" loading=3D"lazy" style=3D"height:=
 313px; width: 414px" class=3D"embedImage-img importedEmbed-img"></div><p>T=
he override column displays at the far right of the Gradebook. Locate the s=
tudent whose grade you want to override and enter a percentage or a letter =
grade in the Override column.</p><p>To delete an overridden grade, click th=
e grade cell and click the <strong>Delete</strong> key.</p><h2 id=3D"view-o=
verride-grade" data-id=3D"view-override-grade">View Override Grade</h2><div=
><img src=3D"https://us.v-cdn.net/6038536/uploads/migrated/5RFDDCV5KA27/b08=
e82c5-c58d-4a64-93c4-7bfe893020e7.png" alt=3D"View Override Grade" height=
=3D"310" width=3D"414" loading=3D"lazy" style=3D"height: 310px; width: 414p=
x" class=3D"embedImage-img importedEmbed-img"></div><p>View the overridden =
grade.</p><h2 id=3D"view-gradebook-viewing-options" data-id=3D"show-or-hide=
-total-and-override-columns">Show or Hide Total and Override Columns</h2><d=
iv><img src=3D"https://us.v-cdn.net/6038536/uploads/migrated/FVUUYB81J4UD/c=
fd55db6-395b-469f-8713-4ccb5cd38e53.png" alt=3D"Show or Hide Total and Over=
ride Columns" height=3D"387" width=3D"855" loading=3D"lazy" style=3D"height=
: 387px; width: 855px" class=3D"embedImage-img importedEmbed-img"></div><p>=
To show or hide the total and override columns, click the <strong>Settings<=
/strong> icon [1] and click the<strong> View Options</strong> tab [2]. </p>=
<p>When the Final Grade Override feature option is enabled, click the <stro=
ng>Hide Total Column and Override Columns</strong> checkbox [3]. Click the =
<strong>Apply Settings</strong> button [4].</p><p><strong>Note:</strong> If=
 the Final Grade Override feature option is disabled, the text in the Show =
section displays Hide Total Column [5]. </p></div></div></div></div></div><=
